# 3.1.1.research.external.q7.per-brain-isolation

## question

how does auth swap per enrolled brain without impact to global auth state? does apiKeyHelper scope to process, or system-wide?

## options

- process-scoped (each terminal can have different auth)
- system-wide (all terminals share auth)
- configurable

## why it matters

determines if rotation in one terminal affects others. if system-wide, need coordination.

## research approach

check apiKeyHelper docs, test with multiple terminals, verify isolation.

## .status

awaited
